#--------------------------
# Description
#--------------------------

# Modify autostart behaviour of the Raspberry Pi so it boots directly into a PCO Live webpage, hides the mouse cursor, and disables pwer management features / screensavers.
# Append to the end of ~/.config/lxsession/LXDE-pi/autostart
# Source: https://github.com/Chalta/Zeitgeist/edit/master/autostart

#--------------------------
# Lines to be appended
#--------------------------


# Trick Chrome into always thinking it close cleanly. So we don't see "Chromium didn't shut down correctly" in case of unplanned power loss.)
@sed -i 's/exit_type\"\:\ \"Crashed/exit_type\"\:\ \"normal/g' /home/pi/.config/chromium/Profile 1/Preferences


#start chromium in full-screen mode, disable infobars and load a default webpage
#NOTE: Edit XXXXXX to your default service type
@chromium-browser --start-fullscreen --disable-infobars https://services.planningcenteronline.com/service_types/XXXXX/plans/after/today/live

# don't blank the video device
@xset s noblank

# disable screen saver
@xset s off

# disable DPMS power management features (sleep).
@xset â€“dpms

# hides pointer when mouse idle for more than X seconds
@unclutter -idle 0.1 -root
